,"1258":"1258","1247":"1247","1213":"1213","1224":"1224","1200":"1200","1177":"1177","1298":"1298","1220":"1220","1175":"1175","1250":"1250","12 August 1247":"12 augustus 1247","Dundonald, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Dundonald, Ayrshire, Schotland","Berwickshire, Scotland":"Berwickshire, Schotland","Scotland":"Schotland","Bonkyl, Berwickshire, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Berwickshire, Schotland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1205–1258":"1205–1258","1200–1247":"1200–1247","1220–1298":"1220–1298","1175–1213":"1175–1213","1177–1250":"1177–1250","1205":"1205","1258":"1258","1247":"1247","1213":"1213","1224":"1224","1200":"1200","1177":"1177","1298":"1298","1220":"1220","1175":"1175","1250":"1250","12 August 1247":"12 August 1247","Dundonald, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Dundonald, Ayrshire, Scotland","Berwickshire, Scotland":"Berwickshire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland","Bonkyl, Berwickshire, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Berwickshire, Scotland, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Douglas","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Scottish: habitational name from any of various places called from their situation on a river named with Gaelic <i>dubh</i> ‘dark, black’ + <i>glas</i> ‘stream’ (a derivative of <i>glas</i> ‘blue’). There are several localities in Scotland and Ireland so named, but the one from which the surname is derived in most if not all cases is Douglas in Lanarkshire 20 miles south of Glasgow, the original stronghold of the influential Douglas family and their retainers.","History: The family taking their name from Douglas in Lanarkshire were of Flemish origin. They rose to great prominence in the 14th and 15th centuries, controlling the earldoms of Douglas, Morton, and Angus, and later, Queensberry."],"variants":[{"name":"Douglass","meanings":["Scottish and English (Durham and Northumbria): variant of   Douglas  .","History: William Douglass, a physician recognized for his identification and description of an epidemic of scarlet fever, was born <i>c.</i> 1691 in Gifford, Haddington County, Scotland, and settled in Boston in 1718. The abolitionist, orator, and journalist Frederick Douglass assumed the name after escaping from slavery in 1838 and traveling to Massachusetts. Son of a white father and a slave with some Indian blood, he was born Frederick Augustus Washington Bailey <i>c.</i> 1817 in Tuckahoe, MD."]}]},{"name":"Beatrix","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From a Late Latin personal name, which was borne by a saint martyred in Rome, together with Saints Faustinus and Simplicius, in the early 4th century. The original form of the name was probably <i>Viatrix</i>, a feminine version of <i>Viator</i> ‘voyager (through life)’, which was a favourite name among early Christians. This was then altered by association with Latin <i>Beatus</i> ‘blessed’ (<i>Via-</i> and <i>Bea-</i> sometimes being pronounced the same in Late Latin).  See also  Beatrice ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Lady Beatrix de Douglas was born in 1205, in Dundonald, Ayrshire, Scotland, her father, William \"Long Legs\" De Douglas, was 30 and her mother, Margaret De Crawford, was 28. She married Randolph De Bonkyll in 1224, in Berwickshire, Scotland. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died in 1258, in Berwickshire, Scotland, at the age of 53."},"et":{"1205–1258":"1205–1258","1200–1247":"1200–1247","1220–1298":"1220–1298","1175–1213":"1175–1213","1177–1250":"1177–1250","1205":"1205","1258":"1258","1247":"1247","1213":"1213","1224":"1224","1200":"1200","1177":"1177","1298":"1298","1220":"1220","1175":"1175","1250":"1250","12 August 1247":"12. august 1247","Dundonald, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Dundonald, Ayrshire, Scotland","Berwickshire, Scotland":"Berwickshire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland","Bonkyl, Berwickshire, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Berwickshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1205–1258":"1205–1258","1200–1247":"1200–1247","1220–1298":"1220–1298","1175–1213":"1175–1213","1177–1250":"1177–1250","1205":"1205","1258":"1258","1247":"1247","1213":"1213","1224":"1224","1200":"1200","1177":"1177","1298":"1298","1220":"1220","1175":"1175","1250":"1250","12 August 1247":"12. elokuuta 1247","Dundonald, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Dundonald, Ayrshire, Scotland","Berwickshire, Scotland":"Berwickshire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland","Bonkyl, Berwickshire, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Berwickshire, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1205–1258":"1205–1258","1200–1247":"1200–1247","1220–1298":"1220–1298","1175–1213":"1175–1213","1177–1250":"1177–1250","1205":"1205","1258":"1258","1247":"1247","1213":"1213","1224":"1224","1200":"1200","1177":"1177","1298":"1298","1220":"1220","1175":"1175","1250":"1250","12 August 1247":"12 août 1247","Dundonald, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Dundonald, Ayrshire, Écosse","Berwickshire, Scotland":"Berwickshire, Écosse","Scotland":"Écosse","Bonkyl, Berwickshire, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Berwickshire, Écosse, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Lady Beatrix de Douglas est née en 1205, à Dundonald, Ayrshire, Écosse, son père, William \"Long Legs\" De Douglas, avait 30 ans et sa mère, Margaret De Crawford, avait 28 ans. Elle a épousé Randolph De Bonkyll en 122